<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Product</b> Solutions</div><h1>Solutions for contractors who want a cleaner commercial operating system.</h1><p class="lead">FCA fits teams that want a smoother revenue path, stronger bid handling, better proposal continuity, and a clearer transition from customer interest into delivery readiness.</p><div class="grid-3 section"><article class="card"><h3>Owner-operators</h3><p>Start with a low-friction package that makes intake and follow-through look more professional immediately.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Growing teams</h3><p>Step into broader coordination across proposals, customer communication, and rollout readiness.</p></article><article class="card auricrux-mark"><h3 class="gold">Enterprise-minded contractors</h3><p>Position FCA as a broader system for commercial continuity, multi-team coordination, and Auricrux-guided scale.</p></article></div></div></main>'

create_page "/pricing" "FCA Pricing" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Commercial</b> Pricing</div><h1>Pricing built to support entry, expansion, and enterprise rollout.</h1><p class="lead">The pricing ladder now gives buyers a clearer spread across low-tier, mid-tier, launch, growth, and enterprise options.</p><div class="grid-5 section"><article class="card plan-card"><div class="eyebrow">Entry</div><h3>Startup Workspace</h3><div class="price">$99/mo</div><p>For owner-operators and very small contractors who need a clean front-end system for intake, bid continuity, and guided next actions.</p><ul class="feature-list"><li>Simple commercial entry point</li><li>Bid intake positioning</li><li>Auricrux buying guidance</li></ul><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/intake/?plan=startup">Choose Startup</a></div></article><article class="card plan-card"><div class="eyebrow">Low / Mid</div><h3>Team Workspace</h3><div class="price">$299/mo</div><p>For smaller active teams that need stronger customer follow-through, proposal movement, and internal coordination without jumping to a large rollout cost.</p><ul class="feature-list"><li>Better sales coordination</li><li>More structured proposal flow</li><li>Broader customer follow-through</li></ul><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/intake/?plan=team">Choose Team</a></div></article><article class="card plan-card"><div class="eyebrow">Launch</div><h3>Pilot Workspace</h3><div class="price">$2,500 one-time</div><p>For guided launch and onboarding with a stronger setup motion, clearer package fit, and a more deliberate first implementation path.</p><ul class="feature-list"><li>Guided implementation</li><li>Commercial-to-operational launch</li><li>Onboarding support</li></ul><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/intake/?plan=pilot">Start Pilot</a></div></article><article class="card plan-card"><div class="eyebrow">Growth</div><h3>Growth Platform</h3><div class="price">$1,500/mo</div><p>For contractors scaling customer coordination, communications coverage, and a broader operating posture.</p><ul class="feature-list"><li>Stronger multi-team coordination</li><li>Communications expansion</li><li>Broader rollout posture</li></ul><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/intake/?plan=growth">Plan Growth</a></div></article><article class="card plan-card auricrux-mark"><div class="eyebrow gold">Enterprise</div><h3 class="gold">Enterprise Rollout</h3><div class="price">$3,500+/mo</div><p>For larger organizations adopting FCA as a broader operating system across commercial, operational, training, and Auricrux-guided execution layers.</p><ul class="feature-list"><li>Enterprise rollout planning</li><li>Broader communications lanes</li><li>Executive Auricrux positioning</li></ul><div class="cta-row"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/intake/?plan=enterprise">Request Enterprise</a></div></article></div></div></main>'

create_page "/about" "About FCA" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Company</b> About</div><h1>FCA is building a contractor operating system that makes the commercial path easier to trust and easier to scale.</h1><p class="lead">Instead of relying on scattered tools for intake, bids, proposal handling, and customer follow-through, FCA is designed to make those moments feel like one connected system.</p><div class="grid-2 section"><article class="card"><h3>Why FCA exists</h3><p>Contractors lose time and revenue when the front-end journey is fragmented. FCA is sold as a cleaner path from first inquiry through proposal and early setup.</p></article><article class="card auricrux-mark"><h3 class="gold">Why Auricrux matters</h3><p>Auricrux gives the experience a clear guide that can explain value, compare tiers, and help move the buyer toward the right next step.</p></article></div></div></main>'

create_page "/contact" "Contact FCA" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Company</b> Contact</div><h1>Talk to FCA about package fit, rollout posture, and activation.</h1><p class="lead">Use the FCA contact channels below to discuss pricing, fit, rollout, or support. These are the active aliases attached to Auricrux.</p><div class="grid-3 section"><article class="card"><h3>Sales</h3><p><span class="code">sales@futurecontractorsofamerica.com</span></p><p>Use for package fit, pricing questions, and activation requests.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>General information</h3><p><span class="code">info@futurecontractorsofamerica.com</span></p><p>Use for general product, company, and public-facing questions.</p></article><article class="card auricrux-mark"><h3 class="gold">Support</h3><p><span class="code">support@futurecontractorsofamerica.com</span></p><p>Use for login, onboarding, or customer-access questions.</p></article></div></div></main>'

create_page "/auricrux" "Meet Auricrux" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="badge-gold">Auricrux · Gold command layer</div><h1>Ask Auricrux about packages, outcomes, rollout, and the best next step.</h1><p class="lead">Auricrux is presented here as a guided buying and onboarding layer. The public experience now uses the Auricrux gold scheme consistently so customers can quickly recognize Auricrux-led surfaces.</p><div class="grid-2 section"><section class="card auricrux-mark"><div class="logo-strip" style="margin-top:0"><div class="auricrux-token">A</div><div><strong class="gold">Auricrux</strong><div class="small">Package guidance and next-step routing</div></div></div><p style="margin-top:16px" class="gold">Ask anything about package fit, Team vs Growth, enterprise readiness, intake, or how FCA helps contractors win and convert more work.</p><div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:16px"><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`Which FCA package fits a small contractor?`)">Small contractor fit</button><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`What is the difference between Team and Growth?`)">Team vs Growth</button><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`When should I choose Enterprise Rollout?`)">Enterprise fit</button><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`What happens after intake?`)">What happens after intake?</button><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`Can FCA help me win and convert more work?`)">Win more work</button><button class="dropbtn" onclick="runPreset(`Which email should I use for pricing and activation?`)">Which email should I use?</button></div><input id="commandInput" class="field" style="margin-top:16px;padding:12px 13px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(212,154,34,.45);background:#07111e;color:#fff;width:100%" placeholder="Ask Auricrux a sales or product question..." /><div class="cta-row"><button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="runCommand()">Send command</button><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/intake/">Start Intake</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/pricing/">View Pricing</a></div><div id="output" class="output">Auricrux ready. Ask about packages, outcomes, rollout, enterprise fit, or the next commercial step.</div></section><aside class="card auricrux-mark"><h2 class="gold">Auricrux-led navigation</h2><div class="list"><div class="row"><span class="dot"></span><div><strong class="gold">Explain value</strong><p>Why FCA helps contractors look sharper and move work forward faster.</p></div></div><div class="row"><span class="dot"></span><div><strong class="gold">Compare tiers</strong><p>Which package best fits the buyer’s stage, size, and urgency.</p></div></div><div class="row"><span class="dot"></span><div><strong class="gold">Route next steps</strong><p>Move into intake, contact, activation, or login with less uncertainty.</p></div></div></div></aside></div></div></main>
<script>
function reply(text){const q=(text||"").toLowerCase();
 if(q.includes("small contractor")||q.includes("startup")) return "Auricrux: Startup Workspace is the cleanest fit for owner-operators and very small contractors who want a professional intake and bid path without heavy overhead. Team Workspace is the better step when a small crew needs more follow-through and coordination.";
 if(q.includes("team")&&q.includes("growth")) return "Auricrux: Team Workspace is the lower-cost step for smaller active teams that need stronger sales and proposal coordination. Growth Platform is for contractors who are scaling communications, team coordination, and rollout breadth more aggressively.";
 if(q.includes("enterprise")) return "Auricrux: Enterprise Rollout is the right fit when FCA needs to support multiple teams, broader communications lanes, more executive visibility, and a bigger adoption motion than a standard growth package can comfortably carry.";
 if(q.includes("win")||q.includes("convert")) return "Auricrux: FCA helps contractors win and convert more work by making intake cleaner, bid posture more visible, proposal follow-through stronger, and the handoff into setup less fragmented.";
 if(q.includes("after intake")) return "Auricrux: After intake, FCA confirms fit, assigns the right package path, and carries the customer toward activation, login, and the first gated product experience.";
 if(q.includes("which email")||q.includes("pricing")||q.includes("activation")) return "Auricrux: Use sales@futurecontractorsofamerica.com for pricing and activation questions, info@futurecontractorsofamerica.com for general questions, and support@futurecontractorsofamerica.com for customer-access help.";
 return "Auricrux: FCA is built to help contractors present a cleaner commercial process from first contact through proposal and early setup. I can help you compare packages, clarify fit, and point you to the best next step.";}
function runPreset(text){document.getElementById("commandInput").value=text;runCommand();}
function runCommand(){const input=document.getElementById("commandInput");document.getElementById("output").textContent=reply(input.value.trim());}
document.getElementById("commandInput").addEventListener("keydown",function(e){if(e.key==="Enter"){runCommand();}})
</script>'

create_page "/intake" "FCA Intake" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Get Started</b> Intake</div><h1>Complete one real customer intake flow.</h1><p class="lead">There is now a single intake path for all customers. Your selected package changes the onboarding branch later, but the intake flow itself is unified.</p><section class="card section"><form id="intakeForm"><div class="form-grid"><div class="field"><label for="plan">Offer</label><select id="plan"><option value="startup">Startup Workspace</option><option value="team">Team Workspace</option><option value="pilot">Pilot Workspace</option><option value="growth">Growth Platform</option><option value="enterprise">Enterprise Rollout</option></select></div><div class="field"><label for="company">Company</label><input id="company" required placeholder="Your company name" /></div><div class="field"><label for="name">Contact name</label><input id="name" required placeholder="Primary contact" /></div><div class="field"><label for="email">Work email</label><input id="email" type="email" required placeholder="name@company.com" /></div><div class="field"><label for="phone">Phone</label><input id="phone" placeholder="Phone number" /></div><div class="field"><label for="size">Company size</label><select id="size"><option>Owner-operator</option><option>2-5 employees</option><option>6-15 employees</option><option>16-50 employees</option><option>50+ employees</option></select></div><div class="field full"><label for="need">Primary need</label><select id="need"><option>Lead intake and bid continuity</option><option>Proposal and award handoff</option><option>Customer coordination and visibility</option><option>Operational rollout with Auricrux support</option><option>Enterprise operating-system rollout</option></select></div><div class="field full"><label for="notes">What do you want FCA to improve first?</label><textarea id="notes" placeholder="Describe the commercial, proposal, communication, or rollout problem you want FCA to solve first."></textarea></div></div><div class="cta-row"><button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Continue to activation</button><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/pricing/">Back to pricing</a></div><div class="status">Your intake creates temporary customer credentials tied to the email you enter, so you can continue as a real customer through the same flow.</div></form></section></div></main>
<script>
const params=new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);const preset=params.get("plan");if(preset){document.getElementById("plan").value=preset;}
function tempPasswordFromEmail(email){const name=(email.split("@")[0]||"customer").replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g,"").slice(0,12)||"customer";return name+"-FCA-2026!";}
document.getElementById("intakeForm").addEventListener("submit",function(e){e.preventDefault();const plan=document.getElementById("plan").value;const company=document.getElementById("company").value;const email=document.getElementById("email").value.trim();const tempPassword=tempPasswordFromEmail(email);const record={email:email.toLowerCase(),password:tempPassword,company:company,plan:plan};localStorage.setItem("fca_temp_customer",JSON.stringify(record));window.location.href="/checkout/?plan="+encodeURIComponent(plan)+"&company="+encodeURIComponent(company)+"&email="+encodeURIComponent(email);});
</script>'

create_page "/checkout" "FCA Checkout & Activation" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Get Started</b> Activation</div><h1>Review your package and activate your path into the gated layer.</h1><p class="lead">This page gives you one activation step for every customer path: review your selected package, apply a code if needed, and continue into login with the temporary credentials created from your intake.</p><section class="card section"><div class="status">Single customer path: intake creates temporary credentials, activation confirms your route, login moves you into the current protected product surface.</div><h2 id="offerTitle" style="margin-top:18px">Selected offer</h2><p id="summary"></p><div id="credentialBox" class="status" style="margin-top:16px"></div><div class="field" style="margin-top:16px"><label for="promo">Activation code</label><input id="promo" placeholder="Enter activation code if you have one" /></div><div class="cta-row"><button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" onclick="applyCode()">Apply code</button><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/login/">Continue to login</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="mailto:sales@futurecontractorsofamerica.com?subject=FCA%20Package%20Activation">Email sales</a></div><div id="promoStatus" class="status" style="margin-top:14px">Founder free-code path: use <span class="code">FCA-FOUNDER-FREE-2026</span> to zero the current package for onboarding and validation.</div></section></div></main>
<script>
const params=new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);const plan=params.get("plan")||"startup";const company=decodeURIComponent(params.get("company")||"your company");const email=decodeURIComponent(params.get("email")||"");const titleMap={startup:"Startup Workspace",team:"Team Workspace",pilot:"Pilot Workspace",growth:"Growth Platform",enterprise:"Enterprise Rollout"};const priceMap={startup:"$99/mo",team:"$299/mo",pilot:"$2,500 one-time",growth:"$1,500/mo",enterprise:"$3,500+/mo"};document.getElementById("offerTitle").textContent=(titleMap[plan]||"FCA Package")+" · "+(priceMap[plan]||"pricing pending");document.getElementById("summary").textContent="Selected for "+company+". Next action: confirm activation, then sign in using the temporary credentials created from your intake.";function tempPasswordFromEmail(email){const name=(email.split("@")[0]||"customer").replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/g,"").slice(0,12)||"customer";return name+"-FCA-2026!";}const cred=email?{email:email.toLowerCase(),password:tempPasswordFromEmail(email)}:null;if(cred){document.getElementById("credentialBox").innerHTML="Temporary customer credentials created:<br/><span class='code'>"+cred.email+"</span><br/><span class='code'>"+cred.password+"</span>";}else{document.getElementById("credentialBox").textContent="No intake record found yet. Complete intake first to generate your temporary credentials.";}function applyCode(){const val=(document.getElementById("promo").value||"").trim();const box=document.getElementById("promoStatus");if(val==="FCA-FOUNDER-FREE-2026"){box.className="status success";box.textContent="Activation code accepted. Your current onboarding path is marked as no-charge for validation and founder use.";}else{box.className="status error";box.textContent="Code not recognized. Use the founder code exactly as issued or email sales for activation help.";}}
</script>'

create_page "/login" "FCA Login" '
<main class="hero-simple"><div class="wrap"><div class="kicker"><b>Access</b> Login</div><h1>Sign in with the customer credentials from your intake.</h1><p class="lead">You now follow the same path as a normal customer: complete intake, receive temporary credentials, activate your route, then sign in.</p><div class="grid-2 section"><article class="card"><h2>Your current credential options</h2><div class="list"><div class="row"><span class="dot"></span><div><strong>Temporary intake-created credentials</strong><p>These are created automatically from the email you enter during intake and shown on the activation page.</p></div></div><div class="row"><span class="dot"></span><div><strong>Launch customer fallback</strong><p>Email: <span class="code">launch.customer@futurecontractorsofamerica.com</span><br/>Password: <span class="code">FCA-Launch-2026!</span></p></div></div></div><p class="small">If you want the true customer path, use intake first and then sign in with the temporary credentials created for that intake.</p></article><aside class="card"><h2>Sign in</h2><form id="loginForm"><div class="field"><label for="email">Work email</label><input id="email" type="email" placeholder="name@company.com" /></div><div class="field"><label for="password">Password</label><input id="password" type="password" placeholder="Enter your password" /></div><div class="cta-row"><button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit" id="signInBtn">Sign in</button></div><div id="statusBox" class="status">Sign in routes into the current protected customer surface.</div></form></aside></div></div></main>
<script>
const FALLBACK={email:"launch.customer@futurecontractorsofamerica.com",password:"FCA-Launch-2026!"};
const form=document.getElementById("loginForm");const email=document.getElementById("email");const password=document.getElementById("password");const box=document.getElementById("statusBox");const btn=document.getElementById("signInBtn");
const intakeRecord=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("fca_temp_customer")||"null");if(intakeRecord){email.value=intakeRecord.email||"";password.value=intakeRecord.password||"";}else{email.value=FALLBACK.email;password.value=FALLBACK.password;}
function setStatus(msg,kind){box.textContent=msg;box.className="status"+(kind?" "+kind:"");}
function isLocalMatch(e,p){const em=(e||"").trim().toLowerCase();const pw=(p||"").trim();if(intakeRecord&&intakeRecord.email===em&&intakeRecord.password===pw){return true;}return em===FALLBACK.email&&pw===FALLBACK.password;}
async function authenticate(payload){try{const response=await fetch('/api/customer-login',{method:'POST',headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},body:JSON.stringify(payload)});const data=await response.json().catch(()=>({ok:false}));if(response.ok&&data.ok){return true;}}catch(e){}return isLocalMatch(payload.email,payload.password);}
form.addEventListener("submit",async function(e){e.preventDefault();btn.disabled=true;setStatus("Authenticating credentials…");const ok=await authenticate({email:email.value,password:password.value});if(ok){setStatus("Login successful. Opening the protected customer surface…","success");setTimeout(()=>window.location.href='/fca-customer-status/',400);}else{setStatus("Credentials did not validate. Complete intake first or use the launch customer fallback credential.","error");}btn.disabled=false;});
</script>'

